onumber\[6pt] &=2 \operatorname{Im}\sum_j  oldsymbol\epsilon_{j,\mathbf{q}
u}^{x*}\, oldsymbol\epsilon_{j,\mathbf{q}
u}^{y} \end{align}

In the above equation $ oldsymbol\epsilon_{j,\mathbf{q}
u}^{x}$ is the x-component of the phonon polarization vector from the j-th atom within the unit cell.

